<h1>EigTool Random Triangular Demo</h1>

<center><img src="../images/randtri_demo.gif" alt="Random Triangular Demo"></center>

<p>This is an upper triangular random matrix whose entries
are drawn from the normal distribution with mean 0 and
variance 1/N.

<p>Unlike a matrix whose entries are all random, taking
non-zero entries only in the upper (or lower) triangle
produces a matrix with a high degree of non-normality [1,2].

<p>[1]: J. M. Varah, "On the separation of two matrices",
     SIAM J. Numer. Anal. 16, pp. 216-222, 1979.
<p>[2]: L. N. Trefethen, "Psuedospectra of matrices", in
     "Numerical Analysis 1991" (Dundee 1991), Longman Sci.
     Tech., Harlow, 1992, 234-266.


